

ITSURA

   This word is from the Spanish hechura.
   it·sú·ra
   shape, form

   itsúra
   the way somebody looks

   may-itsúra
   has an attractive appearance
   Ba’t ganyan ang itsura mo?
   Why do you look like that?
   =What the hell happened to you? You look like a mess.
   Ano ang hitsura ng sugat?
   What does the wound look like?

   spelling variations: itchura, hitsura
